##Q2.3.1
from pyspark.sql import *

#DataFrame as a SQL temporary view
df.createOrReplaceTempView("tmp_view")
#df.show()
# total number of property owners 
num_owners = spark.sql("select host_id, host_name, COUNT(*) as no_of_prop from tmp_view group by host_id, host_name Order by no_of_prop DESC")
# print(num_owners.show())
 ##Get the owners total
no_of_owners=num_owners.count()
multi_prop_owners = spark.sql("select host_id, host_name, COUNT(*) as no_of_prop from tmp_view group by host_id, host_name HAVING no_of_prop>1 Order by no_of_prop DESC")
multi_count = multi_prop_owners.count()
percentage = (float(multi_count)/no_of_owners)*100.0
print("Percentage of owners who rent more than one property: ")
print(percentage)

%pyspark

#needed columns
cols=['id','latitude','longitude','neighbourhood_group']
df_training = df.select(cols)
#df_training.show()
df_training = df_training.na.drop()
df_training = df_training.withColumn("longitude", df_training["longitude"].cast(DoubleType()))
df_training.printSchema()

df_training.createOrReplaceTempView("listings_cols")

df1_training = spark.sql("select neighbourhood_group, count(id) id_count from listings_cols group by neighbourhood_group order by id_count DESC")
df1_training.show()

#ignore minimul popular regions
def valueToInt(value):
    if value=='Central Region': return 1
    elif value=='East Region': return 2
    elif value=='North Region': return 3
    elif value=='North-East Region': return 4
    elif value=='West Region': return  5
    else: return 6
    
udfValueToInt = udf(valueToInt, IntegerType())
df1_training = df_training.withColumn("label_column", udfValueToInt("neighbourhood_group"))

df2_training = df1_training.filter(df1_training['label_column'] < 6)
df2_training.show()

%pyspark
def vectorAssembler(df,impFeatures):
	print(" vectorAssembler start.. ")
	assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=impFeatures,outputCol="features")
	df_new=assembler.transform(df)
	print("vectorAssemblers done.")
	return df_new
impCols=['latitude','longitude']
impdf = df2_training.select(impCols).show()
# Create one feature vector column using latitude and longitude 
dtf=vectorAssembler(df2_training,impCols)
dtf.show()

finalized_data = dtf.select('label_column', 'features')
from pyspark.ml.feature import StandardScaler
scaler = StandardScaler(inputCol='features', outputCol='scaledFeatures', withStd=True, withMean=True)
scalerModel = scaler.fit(finalized_data)
classiFinalData = scalerModel.transform(finalized_data)

# Split the data into training and test sets (20% held out for testing)
(trainingData, testData) = classiFinalData.randomSplit([0.8, 0.2])

trainingData.show()

%pyspark
def Training(trainDF):
	print("Training started")
	lr = LogisticRegression(labelCol="label_column", featuresCol="scaledFeatures",elasticNetParam=0.8, family="multinomial",maxIter=100)
	model=lr.fit(trainDF)
	print("Training completed")
	return model 
	
model = Training(trainingData)

# Get predictions.
predictions = model.transform(testData)

# Predicted data 
predictions.select("prediction", "label_column", "features").show(100)

%pyspark
from pyspark.mllib.evaluation import MulticlassMetrics
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import MulticlassClassificationEvaluator
from pyspark.mllib.evaluation import MultilabelMetrics
from pyspark.mllib.evaluation import MulticlassMetrics, BinaryClassificationMetrics
from pyspark.rdd import RDD

evaluatorRecall = MulticlassClassificationEvaluator(labelCol="label_column", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="weightedRecall")
evaluatorPrecision = MulticlassClassificationEvaluator(labelCol="label_column", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="weightedPrecision")
recall = evaluatorRecall.evaluate(predictions)
precision = evaluatorPrecision.evaluate(predictions)
print("Recall %s" % recall)
print("Precision %s" % precision)

%pyspark

#Q4.6
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

owners = spark.sql("select host_id, host_name, COUNT(*) as rentals from tmp_view group by host_id, host_name Order by rentals DESC")
totOwners=owners.count()
multiowns = spark.sql("select host_id, host_name, COUNT(*) as rentals from tmp_view group by host_id, host_name HAVING rentals>1 Order by rentals DESC")
multiOwners=multiowns.count()
percentageOfMultipleOwners = (float(multiOwners)/totOwners)*100.0
print("Percentage of owners own more than one propert: ")
print(percentageOfMultipleOwners)

labels = 'Multiple property owners', 'Single property owners'
sizes = [percentageOfMultipleOwners, 100 - percentageOfMultipleOwners]
explode = (0.1,0)
fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots()
ax1.pie(sizes, explode=explode, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%',
        shadow=True, startangle=90)
ax1.axis('equal')  # Equal aspect ratio ensures that pie is drawn as a circle.
plt.show()
